The flow is diverted from the reservoir for fish ponds downstream from dam. Diverted flow returns to stream 0.1 mi downstream from gage. site_name: GUADALUPE R ABV HWY 101 A SAN JOSE CA
wr_report_remarks: Flow regulated by Lexington Reservoir 12 mi upstream and by Calero, Almaden, and Guadalupe Reservoirs, and Lake Elsman (combined usable capacity, about 42,000 acre-ft), with water released during summer for percolation in spreading basins on tributaries. Diversions into the above impoundments come from San Luis Reservoir (part of the San Felipe Project), from the South Bay Aqueduct, and from the Hetch Hetchy Aqueduct. There are upstream diversions by the San Jose Water Works for urban use. In addition, an off-stream holding basin located approximately 150 ft downstream collects runoff from part of San Jose Airport and periodically releases water into the stream for a few minutes each day at low flows.
